1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,556
This series is crafted for
the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,796
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events
depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,636
They are not designed to allude to any particular
entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,620
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:26,180 --> 00:00:32,196
♫ I never know what love is like ♫

7
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:36,996
♫ All my life, never once
have I experienced it ♫

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,340
♫ No one to take that place in my heart ♫

9
00:00:41,580 --> 00:00:47,556
♫ But now that I've met you,
my heart begins to glow ♫

10
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:52,316
♫ What feeling is this?
Why is my heart fluttering? ♫

11
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:56,436
♫ And I just can't control it. ♫

12
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:00,276
♫ What happened to my heart right now? ♫

13
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:04,116
♫ I can't control it when you're around ♫

14
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:10,300
♫ This heart…it stops at you ♫

15
00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,316
♫ Is this love? Is that what they call it? ♫

16
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,716
♫ When my heart starts to waver ♫

17
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:23,356
♫ Like a stream of water
slowly pouring over my heart ♫

18
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:26,436
♫ From dusk till dawn, you're
never far from my sight ♫

19
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:30,836
♫ Or is this love? Are
you that someone... ♫

20
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:34,316
♫ ...who's destined to be with me? ♫

21
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:40,476
♫ Is this really happening?
I really want to know ♫

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,716
♫ 'Cos you now hold a
special place in my heart ♫

23
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:46,420
[Waves of Deception] ♫ 'Cos you
now hold a special place in my heart ♫

24
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,576
[Previously]
Everything will be over, right?

25
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,460
You and Kirk haven't signed
the marriage certificate yet.

26
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,660
You can still change your mind, dear,

27
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:58,300
I don't think I can marry him.

28
00:01:58,930 --> 00:01:59,930
I'm sorry, Dad.

29
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:01,760
But this place is quite far away.

30
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:04,060
I don't think anyone can find us, right?

31
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,360
Hello, Lada.

32
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,260
Please tell Miss Apo that,

33
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,360
if she really forgives
me, please let me go.

34
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:15,400
Please leave me alone.
I don't have feelings for you anymore.

35
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,960
Please come back and
be the sunshine in my life.

36
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:25,300
I'm sorry, Miss Apo.
I've come too far to turn back.

37
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,260
Is there something wrong, Boss?

38
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,200
Nothing.

39
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,330
Tomorrow at ten, you have a meeting with…

40
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:30,260
Lada.

41
00:03:31,060 --> 00:03:32,060
Mum.

42
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:37,400
Last one now.

43
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:40,560
Done.

44
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:52,900
Why do you keep pushing
her away if you love her?

45
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,600
What do you mean?

46
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:07,660
I'm sorry. The night before,
I happened to see you talking to Miss Apo.

47
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,000
You know her too?

48
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:22,196
I once heard your dad scolding
Pat for losing to Miss Apo,

49
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:26,580
Mr. Adisorn's daughter, the
owner of your father's rival hotel.

50
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,500
You love her, don't you?

51
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:39,560
No, Mum.

52
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:45,500
Then I guess it's because of me.

53
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:53,060
You can't live life the way
you want because of me.

54
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:57,620
You should worry about
yourself too, sweetie.

55
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,200
It's not because of you at all.

56
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,300
Then why did you reject her?

57
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,276
Even if you hadn't done anything,

58
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:13,780
Dad and Pat would still use me to hurt
Miss Apo and the Watin Group anyway.

59
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:25,460
So, the reason you turned her down
isn't because you don't love her,

60
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,620
but rather because you want
to protect her, is that right?

61
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,800
It's probably best to leave it be.

62
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:39,900
She'll soon forget about me.

63
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:43,659
I'll also get to live my life the way I want.

64
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,300
And everything will be over.

65
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:53,060
Please don't worry, okay?

66
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:58,460
It's all right, Mum. Don't worry.

67
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,140
I'll go back to fixing the door.

68
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:41,580
[Incoming call]

69
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:51,180
[Miss Preem]

70
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,200
Hello, Miss Preem.

71
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:04,260
What was that, again?

72
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,300
Boss has resigned.

73
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,130
What happened?

74
00:07:08,460 --> 00:07:10,360
Why did she resign?

75
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:13,176
Since she came back, she's done nothing
but sitting and moping around.

76
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:16,120
Big Boss couldn't stand seeing her
like that, so he gave her a reprimand.

77
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,800
It got Boss so offended
she decided to quit.

78
00:07:35,930 --> 00:07:36,930
Miss Apo.

79
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:43,100
Lada…what are you doing here?

80
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:48,600
Miss Preem told me you've resigned.

81
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Let's go.

82
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,260
Go where?

83
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,200
To talk to your father.

84
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:01,660
I'm not going to let
you quit no matter what.

85
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,260
From now on, you no longer work here.

86
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:20,660
What do you mean?

87
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:23,716
I know she rejected you,

88
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:27,540
but my girl isn't someone who would
sit around looking miserable like this.

89
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,400
What do you want me to do then?

90
00:08:32,860 --> 00:08:33,860
Fight for her.

91
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:38,059
Make her accept your feelings.

92
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:42,299
I can't fight anymore, Dad.

93
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,300
Miss Preem!

94
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,660
Miss Preem!

95
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:53,760
Yes, Big Boss?

96
00:08:56,300 --> 00:09:00,930
Call Lada and tell her Nam has
resigned from her position as the CEO.

97
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:06,360
Why would you ask her to do that?

98
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,730
Lada wouldn't care anyway.

99
00:09:13,930 --> 00:09:20,500
Do you wanna bet? Let's
see if she'd care or not.

100
00:09:23,260 --> 00:09:23,837
Let's go.

101
00:09:23,861 --> 00:09:25,540
No, Lada. Stop.

102
00:09:28,730 --> 00:09:29,730
I'm not going anywhere.

103
00:09:31,330 --> 00:09:33,500
I've lost all motivation to do anything.

104
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:36,560
But you love your job so much.

105
00:09:37,530 --> 00:09:39,130
Are you really going to quit?

106
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,000
Do you even care?

107
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:46,000
I don't want to ruin your life.

108
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,100
Don't worry.

109
00:09:51,530 --> 00:09:53,260
If my life would be ruined,

110
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,100
it'd entirely be because of me.

111
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,960
I'd never blame you.

112
00:10:00,930 --> 00:10:02,960
And I'll never let
anyone do that to you too.

113
00:10:07,130 --> 00:10:10,560
I quit because I'm feeling too exhausted.

114
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:13,330
Please excuse me.

115
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:19,720
If you don't want anyone to blame
me for causing you to be like this,

116
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:22,000
then please go back to work.

117
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:24,580
I'm begging you.

118
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,260
You're talented.

119
00:10:33,530 --> 00:10:36,100
The Watin Group has
come this far because of you.

120
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,330
You've overcome so many obstacles.

121
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:47,660
You'll soon forget about me.

122
00:10:52,130 --> 00:10:53,290
And it will be just a memory.

123
00:10:55,660 --> 00:10:56,860
I don't know.

124
00:10:58,860 --> 00:11:01,360
I can't imagine my life without you, Lada.

125
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,300
Please stop it.

126
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:08,930
You already saw how much
you'd suffer if you love me.

127
00:11:09,930 --> 00:11:13,980
Don't forget I'm still the
Wachara Group's daughter.

128
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,530
Not to mention that my brother
also tried to sabotage you.

129
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:20,360
Why do you still want me back?

130
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,160
It doesn't matter at all, Lada.

131
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:29,060
Doing business means
we can never avoid having problems.

132
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:38,060
But at least if I have to face a dead end,
I'd rather face it with you beside me.

133
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:44,660
Why do you have to love me this much?

134
00:11:56,930 --> 00:11:59,100
Now you know I love you the most, huh?

135
00:12:12,530 --> 00:12:13,560
Please marry me.

136
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,860
Don't turn me down again, Lada.

137
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,600
It's Nam.

138
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,600
Don't worry, Lada.

139
00:13:11,130 --> 00:13:16,660
If you trust in me and in our love,

140
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,760
we'll finally get through it together.

141
00:13:23,730 --> 00:13:26,330
I promise I'll never let go of your hand.

142
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,930
Please marry me.

143
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,740
You already said it.

144
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:47,260
Don't ever let me down, or make me cry.

145
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:51,460
I promise.

146
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:54,260
We're married now.

147
00:15:13,330 --> 00:15:15,490
What kind of groom kisses
their bride on the forehead?

148
00:15:16,330 --> 00:15:17,740
Where should I kiss then?

149
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:45,400
It's raining so hard, how can I go home?

150
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,930
Then don't.

151
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:53,200
I can't do that. Mum will be so worried.

152
00:15:57,760 --> 00:16:02,660
I never like the rain
when you're not around.

153
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:05,100
Were you that lonely?

154
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:14,560
I miss you so much.

155
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,000
I miss you too.

156
00:17:00,660 --> 00:17:01,700
What's wrong?

157
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,530
I'm hungry.

158
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:08,900
I haven't eaten anything since I left Nan.

159
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,060
I think the kitchen is closed now.

160
00:17:19,099 --> 00:17:20,359
Can you eat me instead?

161
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,329
What kind of answer do you want?

162
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,360
Just be honest.

163
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:37,660
[Chonlada &amp; Apo]

164
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Nate!

165
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:33,660
Wow, Lada.

166
00:22:36,380 --> 00:22:37,780
Lada!

167
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:38,700
Pretty?

168
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:40,980
You look stunning. Let me see.

169
00:22:43,260 --> 00:22:45,596
Well, you don't look so bad yourself.

170
00:22:45,620 --> 00:22:49,180
If you had dressed up like this every day, you
would've got yourself a boyfriend long ago.

171
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:53,500
I only dress up this fancy
because it's your wedding.

172
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:04,020
Thank you so much, Nate. Without you,
I wouldn't have been here today.

173
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:08,060
Thank you for always supporting me
and giving me a reality check.

174
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:15,100
Congratulations. You're the
most beautiful bride I've ever seen.

175
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,660
Don't you agree, Miss Apo?

176
00:23:29,130 --> 00:23:30,360
What's the tea, ladies?

177
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:33,300
Nothing.

178
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:35,540
It's a secret.

179
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:39,330
Is there anything I still don't know?

180
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,760
Do you want to know her secret, Lada?

181
00:23:45,530 --> 00:23:47,000
What, Dad?

182
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,800
Yes, I do.

183
00:23:49,260 --> 00:23:54,060
That you tricked her into
believing you had quit your job.

184
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:57,760
But that was your plan.

185
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,276
Well, I had to do something or else,

186
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:02,276
our Watin Group might
have gone out of business.

187
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:05,780
Because all the CEO did was sitting
at her desk like an abandoned dog.

188
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:11,660
Wow, I never thought
you could be this cunning.

189
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:17,200
Hey, if I hadn't done that, you
would've left me forever then.

190
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:24,140
Aww, looks like the tigress has already
been tamed and turned into a kitten.

191
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:31,636
Excuse me, sir. The
guests are starting to arrive.

192
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:34,876
Shall Boss and Miss Lada
go get ready at the backdrop?

193
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,940
Many guests are now
asking for the wedding couple.

194
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:01,380
Okay, smile. Again, please.

195
00:25:03,260 --> 00:25:04,540
One more.

196
00:25:04,930 --> 00:25:08,140
That's it. Thank you.

197
00:25:08,330 --> 00:25:09,506
May you both find a lot of happiness.

198
00:25:09,530 --> 00:25:10,276
Thank you, Mum.

199
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:11,300
Thank you, Mum.

200
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:12,530
Thank you, Dad.

201
00:25:18,060 --> 00:25:20,580
Nate! Let's take a picture.

202
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,020
Ready?

203
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:24,460
Beautiful.

204
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:26,960
There you go.

205
00:25:27,330 --> 00:25:28,760
I'll talk to you later.

206
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:29,900
Don't get drunk.

207
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:31,360
Congratulations.

208
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:32,500
Thank you.

209
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:36,836
One more, please.

210
00:25:36,860 --> 00:25:37,956
That's it.

211
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:39,116
Thank you so much.

212
00:25:39,140 --> 00:25:41,276
Congratulations.

213
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,236
Congratulations, Boss.

214
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:44,716
Congrats, girl. Hello.

215
00:25:44,740 --> 00:25:46,196
Just a moment.

216
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:49,516
- Thank you.
- Congrats to you both.

217
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:50,540
Thank you.

218
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:58,300
Nam, why are there so many guests?

219
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:02,500
I thought I told you not
to invite a lot of people.

220
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:10,420
When everyone hears that we're getting
married, they all want to come to our wedding.

221
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:15,436
But I remember telling
only Miss Preem about it.

222
00:26:15,460 --> 00:26:18,740
I even emphasized that I
wanted to keep it private.

223
00:26:20,260 --> 00:26:25,700
Sorry, I happened to tell Miss
Nussara and Miss Wadee too.

224
00:26:27,460 --> 00:26:31,930
That explains why many
people are attending.

225
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:34,996
Wow! You look gorgeous!

226
00:26:35,020 --> 00:26:37,260
Such a perfect couple!

227
00:26:37,660 --> 00:26:39,196
Congratulations, Boss!

228
00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:42,340
Congratulations, Miss
Chonlada! So perfect together.

229
00:26:43,130 --> 00:26:46,460
Thank you. You can just
call me Lada like before.

230
00:26:47,620 --> 00:26:55,620
Oh no, we can't do that, La-I mean, Miss
Chonlada. Since you're now Boss's wife,

231
00:26:55,940 --> 00:26:57,780
we can't call you like before.

232
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:01,956
Really, Nuch. That's not what
you said when we were in the car.

233
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:05,156
You said you just found out Miss
Chonlada is the Wachara Group's daughter.

234
00:27:05,180 --> 00:27:08,020
And that we shouldn't call her Miss
because technically she's our rival.

235
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:10,740
What? No way.

236
00:27:12,060 --> 00:27:13,516
That's not what I said.

237
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:15,460
I said…

238
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:18,730
Even though Miss Lada is
the Wachara Group's daughter,

239
00:27:19,130 --> 00:27:22,300
but if Boss has chosen to marry her;

240
00:27:22,730 --> 00:27:24,876
it means she's also one
of us, the Watin Group.

241
00:27:24,900 --> 00:27:27,060
So, it's the right thing
to address her as Miss.

242
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:31,540
Miss Wadee was busy talking on
the phone and probably misheard it.

243
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:33,476
Sorry, my bad.

244
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:35,036
Might have misheard it indeed.

245
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:36,356
It's all right.

246
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:39,220
You can call me Lada like you used to.

247
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:42,756
You're so kind, Miss Chonlada.

248
00:27:42,780 --> 00:27:44,660
As always.

249
00:27:45,020 --> 00:27:47,660
Truly the lady of the house.

250
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:53,500
I think Boss's and Miss Chonlada's boots
are probably soaking wet by now.

251
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,276
Enough with the flattering. Let's
hurry up and take some pictures.

252
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:57,716
There are people waiting.

253
00:27:57,740 --> 00:28:01,036
Aw, Miss Preem, you're doing
such an excellent job as her assistant.

254
00:28:01,060 --> 00:28:03,620
You're helping her not only with
work but also with the wedding.

255
00:28:04,730 --> 00:28:06,730
I'm also hoping for the
same thing as you two are.

256
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:09,476
I want to impress Boss and Miss Lada,

257
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:11,980
so that they might give me a
handsome bonus at year's end.

258
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:13,516
Oh, us too!

259
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:16,716
All right, enough with
banter. Let's take a picture.

260
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:18,196
Okay, Boss.

261
