you to have this bouquet.

400
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:59,060
I hope you'll finally find the
love you've been looking for.

401
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:03,900
Thank you.

402
00:41:15,020 --> 00:41:16,530
Are you single, Miss Lom?

403
00:41:16,900 --> 00:41:17,797
Are you already taken?

404
00:41:17,821 --> 00:41:19,340
Pardon? Are you taken?

405
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:20,517
No, not yet.

406
00:41:20,541 --> 00:41:22,460
I see. She's still looking.

407
00:41:23,700 --> 00:41:24,700
Are you single?

408
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:27,360
Are you single?

409
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:50,930
Where are you taking me, Rose?

410
00:41:51,130 --> 00:41:52,800
I haven't told Nam I'm with you.

411
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:54,360
This way.

412
00:42:05,930 --> 00:42:08,260
I just need to have a few
words with you in private.

413
00:42:08,530 --> 00:42:10,760
It's almost time for the
bridal bed ceremony, isn't it?

414
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,860
Yes, in about half an hour.

415
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:20,180
Don't worry, I already
sent Din to tutor Nam.

416
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:23,400
What do you mean?

417
00:42:23,930 --> 00:42:25,540
It's your first night together.

418
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:30,716
Honestly, Din and I are
quite concerned for you.

419
00:42:30,740 --> 00:42:35,420
Nam might be able to quit being workaholic
and finally end up with you.

420
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:38,360
I hear a 'but' there.

421
00:42:39,860 --> 00:42:43,820
But someone who's been so obsessed with work
all her life is probably only good at work.

422
00:42:44,260 --> 00:42:50,580
For a nerd like her, it's possible she might
get too nervous and doesn't know what to do.

423
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:59,540
Oh, Rose. I think you have
misunderstood something.

424
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:04,460
We shouldn't judge
people by their appearance.

425
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:08,330
What do you mean?

426
00:43:09,660 --> 00:43:11,300
Nam isn't a nerd.

427
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:15,100
Come again?

428
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:22,180
And it's not just work that she's good at.
I can confirm it.

429
00:43:33,700 --> 00:43:36,600
I'm glad you can make it to my wedding.

430
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:41,040
You came to my office to give
me the invitation card yourself.

431
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,360
How could I not come?

432
00:43:46,700 --> 00:43:49,260
Where's Mei?

433
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:53,700
She couldn't make it.

434
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,100
Anyway, I'm so happy for you that
you get to marry the person you love.

435
00:44:01,500 --> 00:44:03,940
I wish you lots of love and happiness.

436
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:08,140
Are you all right?

437
00:44:08,860 --> 00:44:11,500
You look like something
is bothering your mind.

438
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:14,360
It's nothing.

439
00:44:15,300 --> 00:44:21,180
By the way, the maid at Dad's house told me
you went there to visit Dad.

440
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:18,930
You look so beautiful today.

441
00:45:20,860 --> 00:45:22,530
So do you.

442
00:45:25,730 --> 00:45:28,200
I'm sorry we have to
stay here on our first night.

443
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,160
I couldn't get our home done in time.

444
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:33,730
It doesn't matter at all.

445
00:45:34,060 --> 00:45:37,700
Having you here with
me is more than enough.

446
00:45:41,300 --> 00:45:45,540
Then, should we do…

447
00:45:47,460 --> 00:45:49,420
Something…

448
00:45:50,100 --> 00:45:52,500
Having your mind in the gutter again.

449
00:45:56,730 --> 00:46:00,530
I promise I'll make you feel
special and always keep you happy.

450
00:46:03,300 --> 00:46:08,560
Having you beside me already
makes me happy and feel so special.

451
00:53:12,500 --> 00:53:13,500
Babe!

452
00:53:14,300 --> 00:53:15,300
Making fun of me?

453
00:53:15,360 --> 00:53:16,800
Making fun of me?

454
00:53:18,560 --> 00:53:21,200
I just don't want Boss to get up late.

455
00:53:22,660 --> 00:53:29,460
Well, it's a holiday and I also get to be
with my baby. Why should I get up early?

456
00:53:32,100 --> 00:53:35,300
Then, have fun going back to your sleep.

457
00:53:36,560 --> 00:53:37,560
Huh?

458
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:39,600
Where are you going?

459
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:41,700
Where are you going?

460
00:53:42,600 --> 00:53:43,930
To do some activities.

461
00:53:44,500 --> 00:53:47,100
We've come all the way to Nan.
Are you just going to stay inside?

462
00:53:50,960 --> 00:53:51,960
What activities?

463
00:53:53,300 --> 00:53:55,300
Don't you want to rest anymore?

464
00:53:55,940 --> 00:53:58,560
I do, but I don't want to be alone.

465
00:54:00,130 --> 00:54:04,900
Then, let's go do some outdoor activities
and come back to rest together, okay?

466
00:54:06,300 --> 00:54:10,076
Get up. Let's go shower. Come!

467
00:54:10,100 --> 00:54:13,820
Before that, let's warm up
by doing an indoor activity first.

468
00:54:58,500 --> 00:55:03,796
♫ Since that day you came into
my life, I've started to realise… ♫

469
00:55:03,820 --> 00:55:07,700
♫ What it's like to be
someone who matters ♫

470
00:55:08,020 --> 00:55:13,740
♫ Feeling so warm whenever I see you ♫

471
00:55:14,060 --> 00:55:16,916
♫ Who often stays close to me ♫

472
00:55:16,940 --> 00:55:21,516
♫ I just want you to know ♫

473
00:55:21,540 --> 00:55:28,436
♫ This feeling that's happening inside ♫

474
00:55:28,460 --> 00:55:31,556
♫ I don't want to hide it anymore ♫

475
00:55:31,580 --> 00:55:35,420
♫ I guess I'll have to tell you ♫

476
00:55:35,700 --> 00:55:39,940
♫ You're the one that change my life ♫

477
00:55:40,620 --> 00:55:44,836
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone ♫

478
00:55:44,860 --> 00:55:47,316
♫ Thank you so much ♫

479
00:55:47,340 --> 00:55:50,476
♫ For making my life meaningful ♫

480
00:55:50,500 --> 00:55:56,420
♫ How lucky I am to have you ♫

481
00:55:57,740 --> 00:55:59,260
[Love you]

482
00:56:17,600 --> 00:56:19,860
Your order is here, my darling.

483
00:56:23,460 --> 00:56:24,460
Thank you.

484
00:56:34,060 --> 00:56:36,460
And here's the bill.

485
00:56:41,160 --> 00:56:42,160
So cute.

486
00:56:43,660 --> 00:56:46,460
You said I should cut off
from social media while we're here.

487
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:48,460
How come you still bring work here?

488
00:56:50,330 --> 00:56:55,500
I just need to go over some
details. Nothing serious.

489
00:56:56,860 --> 00:56:58,060
I'm curious.

490
00:57:00,300 --> 00:57:01,300
About what?

491
00:57:01,600 --> 00:57:06,930
What it'd be like if a workaholic like you
decided to quit working for real.

492
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:15,020
Back then, there would've been nothing else
on my mind except you.

493
00:57:16,060 --> 00:57:17,940
Are you saying that to please me?

494
00:57:19,940 --> 00:57:22,540
I'm serious. I really mean it.

495
00:57:23,860 --> 00:57:25,740
Your skill in sweet
talking has improved a lot.

496
00:57:26,730 --> 00:57:28,460
And in eating something spicy too.

497
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:30,200
Are you sure?

498
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:34,180
You could hardly hide it when you
ate the green chilli dip this morning.

499
00:57:38,160 --> 00:57:39,500
I mean you.

500
00:57:41,530 --> 00:57:42,700
Me? What about me?

501
00:57:44,930 --> 00:57:45,930
Hot.

502
00:57:48,380 --> 00:57:50,460
Since when have you
become such a perv like this?

503
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:52,900
It's true though.

504
00:57:55,800 --> 00:58:03,800
You're like that tiny chilli.
Small but fierce. Hot and spicy.

505
00:58:08,000 --> 00:58:09,260
Other people might hear you.

506
00:58:09,900 --> 00:58:11,380
What's wrong with that?

507
00:58:16,260 --> 00:58:21,300
Come. You've worked hard all day.
Let me give you a massage.

508
00:58:22,220 --> 00:58:23,220
Thank you.

509
00:58:34,160 --> 00:58:35,800
- Lada.
- Let me see who sent it.

510
00:58:36,300 --> 00:58:37,460
Is it Miss Preem?

511
00:58:39,940 --> 00:58:44,340
The Downfall of Wachara Group.
A five-star hotel going bankrupt.

512
00:58:57,860 --> 00:59:02,500
Wat, what's going on?
What are all these for?

513
00:59:03,500 --> 00:59:06,900
Pat forged Dad's signature to embezzle
money and move it to another country.

514
00:59:07,260 --> 00:59:10,396
He also used the hotel's name to sign the
guarantee agreement for another company.

515
00:59:10,420 --> 00:59:13,500
That company has run away.
So, our hotel must pay for it.

516
00:59:14,330 --> 00:59:17,500
Do you know which company Mr. Pheempat
has signed this agreement with?

517
00:59:18,160 --> 00:59:22,876
It's Pat's. He hired someone as a nominee
to start up this company.

518
00:59:22,900 --> 00:59:27,596
So, basically, he set up a company to get
a loan by using our hotel as a guarantor.

519
00:59:27,620 --> 00:59:29,740
And he has never told anyone about it.

520
00:59:31,560 --> 00:59:34,000
Do other executives at
the hotel know about this?

521
00:59:34,400 --> 00:59:37,300
Yes, but Pat just paid them hush money.

522
00:59:38,260 --> 00:59:41,580
Dad and I had only found out when
we received summons for the lawsuit.

523
00:59:43,400 --> 00:59:45,000
How could he do that to us?

524
00:59:45,700 --> 00:59:47,330
He resented Dad for never trusting him.

525
00:59:48,460 --> 00:59:52,700
Dad sold off Pat's hotel. So, Pat
wanted to destroy the Wachara Group.

526
00:59:57,130 --> 01:00:00,180
What about Dad? Where's he now?

527
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:04,277
Dad!

528
01:00:04,301 --> 01:00:05,560
Dad! Dad!

529
01:00:09,700 --> 01:00:10,376
Dad!

530
01:00:10,400 --> 01:00:11,400
Dad! Dad!

531
01:00:11,460 --> 01:00:12,460
Dad!

532
01:00:14,330 --> 01:00:15,660
Dad! Are you okay?

533
01:00:15,860 --> 01:00:21,340
- Dad! Are you okay?
- Wat, what happened to him? Dad!

534
01:00:21,660 --> 01:00:22,437
Dad!

535
01:00:22,461 --> 01:00:24,596
Wat, what happened to him? Dad!

536
01:00:24,620 --> 01:00:30,236
- Dad!
- Talk to me, Dad!

537
01:00:30,260 --> 01:00:31,260
Dad!

538
01:00:31,300 --> 01:00:32,300
Dad!

539
01:00:32,460 --> 01:00:35,140
Daddy!

540
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:36,000
Dad!

541
01:00:36,130 --> 01:00:37,676
Dad!

542
01:00:37,700 --> 01:00:39,260
Daddy!

543
01:00:55,500 --> 01:00:56,500
Doctor,

544
01:00:57,060 --> 01:00:58,200
how's my father doing?

545
01:00:58,800 --> 01:01:00,700
The operation has gone well.

546
01:01:01,500 --> 01:01:03,730
I already removed the
blood clot from his brain.

547
01:01:03,900 --> 01:01:04,900
But I'm afraid.

548
01:01:07,500 --> 01:01:09,580
I'll have to be honest here.

549
01:01:10,180 --> 01:01:12,740
The blood clot has somehow
damaged some parts of the brain

550
01:01:13,140 --> 01:01:16,020
and it might cause the patient
to suffer from physical fatigue,

551
01:01:16,820 --> 01:01:19,100
or a far worse symptom.

552
01:01:22,200 --> 01:01:23,500
What do you mean, Doctor?

553
01:01:33,060 --> 01:01:34,060
Yes, Mum.

554
01:01:34,780 --> 01:01:38,860
If there's any update from the doctor,
I'll let you know right away.

555
01:01:41,160 --> 01:01:42,160
Yes.

556
01:01:44,460 --> 01:01:45,460
Goodbye.

557
01:01:56,400 --> 01:01:57,530
Is that your mum?

558
01:01:59,260 --> 01:02:00,260
Yes.

559
01:02:00,460 --> 01:02:02,300
I still don't know how to tell her,

560
01:02:02,530 --> 01:02:05,000
that Dad might be paralysed.

561
01:02:07,960 --> 01:02:11,300
At least, Mr. Pheemdet is still with us.

562
01:02:13,330 --> 01:02:16,400
I really don't get it. How
could Pat do this to his family?

563
01:02:20,800 --> 01:02:24,300
Lom said the police already issued
an arrest warrant for Mr. Pheempat.

564
01:02:25,860 --> 01:02:29,760
But Wat said Pat already left
the country many weeks ago.

565
01:02:33,060 --> 01:02:34,360
I'm sure we'll find a way out.

566
01:02:35,560 --> 01:02:36,730
Don't worry, Lada.

567
01:02:38,330 --> 01:02:39,800
I'll do everything to help.

568
01:02:42,900 --> 01:02:45,260
I really don't know how I could help Dad.

569
01:02:46,660 --> 01:02:51,300
I guess what he used to say is true-that a
daughter like me is useless to the company.

570
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:57,200
Don't look down on yourself like that.

571
01:02:58,000 --> 01:02:59,400
You can do it. I know you can.

572
01:03:00,400 --> 01:03:03,960
You mightn't be able to do much
for the Wachara Group right now.

573
01:03:05,060 --> 01:03:07,060
But there's another way to help them.

574
01:03:09,960 --> 01:03:11,260
How?

575
01:03:16,600 --> 01:03:17,930
I can't do that.

576
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:24,180
Lada, you used to be
Miss Preem's assistant.

577
01:03:24,780 --> 01:03:29,460
Now I only need you to help manage
the hotel, you can definitely do it.

578
01:03:31,900 --> 01:03:34,530
But it's different. I was
only an assistant back then.

579
01:03:35,160 --> 01:03:37,300
But to be an executive, that's…

580
01:03:37,580 --> 01:03:38,980
Your bowl of wanton is here.

581
01:03:39,340 --> 01:03:40,460
Thank you.

582
01:03:41,530 --> 01:03:45,620
You suddenly want me to work
as an executive, I can't do it.

583
01:03:45,980 --> 01:03:47,556
I don't have enough experience.

584
01:03:47,580 --> 01:03:50,660
If your father knows, he'd surely disagree.

585
01:03:51,400 --> 01:03:53,960
It's him who came up with this idea, Lada.

586
01:03:54,900 --> 01:03:59,820
We're opening up a new branch.
I'll have to look after it there.

587
01:04:00,900 --> 01:04:04,100
I won't have time for
the hotel here in Hua Hin.

588
01:04:04,730 --> 01:04:07,000
That's why my dad wants
you to look after it for me.

589
01:04:09,300 --> 01:04:10,800
I still think it's not a good idea.

590
01:04:11,400 --> 01:04:13,040
What would other people think about this?

591
01:04:13,730 --> 01:04:17,660
They'd probably say you
and Big Boss aren't being fair.

592
01:04:20,200 --> 01:04:24,620
The more you're afraid people would
think you're using connections as my wife,

593
01:04:25,600 --> 01:04:27,740
the more you should take this position.

594
01:04:27,930 --> 01:04:32,940
So that you can prove to them that
my dad and I didn't pick the wrong person.

595
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:34,996
But I…

596
01:04:35,020 --> 01:04:41,060
If you can do this, you'll be able
to help the Wachara Group too.

597
01:04:42,730 --> 01:04:43,820
How?

598
01:04:45,130 --> 01:04:48,660
The Wachara Group
might already be closed dow.

599
01:04:49,300 --> 01:04:53,200
But if you take my place and
successfully manage my hote

600
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:57,240
you'll be able to establish the new
Wachara Group and bring back your empire.

601
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:09,780
It's also a chance to prove to Mr. Pheemdet
that you also belong to the Wachara Group.

602
01:05:11,600 --> 01:05:14,740
You can do it. Trust me.

603
01:05:21,900 --> 01:05:26,860
But right now, let's eat.
The food is getting cold.

604
01:05:32,620 --> 01:05:33,860
Eat up.

605
01:05:47,600 --> 01:05:49,200
Welcome, Boss Lada.

606
01:05:51,760 --> 01:05:53,700
Do you have to be so formal, Miss Preem?

607
01:05:56,660 --> 01:05:58,260
I didn't tell her to do it.

608
01:06:01,930 --> 01:06:05,916
When our staff know you'll be
helping Boss looking after this hotel,

609
01:06:05,940 --> 01:06:09,220
they all willingly agree
to call you Boss Lada.

610
01:06:09,560 --> 01:06:13,460
And please don't worry that we
might think you're using connections.

611
01:06:13,930 --> 01:06:16,560
We trust Boss's and Big Boss's decisions.

612
01:06:16,860 --> 01:06:20,330
Whatever choices they've made,
we have absolutely no doubt in them.

613
01:06:22,330 --> 01:06:23,330
Thank you.

614
01:06:25,100 --> 01:06:26,980
If you'd excuse me, I'll
get back to work then.

615
01:06:40,330 --> 01:06:44,000
This room will be your office from now on.

616
01:06:46,560 --> 01:06:51,130
Why is my office in the same room as yours?

617
01:06:52,530 --> 01:06:57,460
Well, in case you have any questions,
you can always ask me right away.

618
01:06:59,200 --> 01:07:06,420
Besides, having you around
could help me focus at work.

619
01:07:07,730 --> 01:07:08,730
Do you like it?

620
01:07:10,700 --> 01:07:11,700
Yes.

621
01:07:18,100 --> 01:07:19,300
Thank you so much.

622
01:07:20,200 --> 01:07:25,760
I promise I'll work hard and won't let
you and Big Boss down for trusting in me.

623
01:07:27,260 --> 01:07:28,360
Don't do it for me.

624
01:07:29,500 --> 01:07:30,900
Do it for our hotel.

625
01:07:32,460 --> 01:07:33,660
And not just the hotel.

626
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:36,900
I'm also yours.

627
01:07:41,530 --> 01:07:42,660
Thank you, Babe.

628
01:07:44,760 --> 01:07:46,000
What was that?

629
01:07:47,860 --> 01:07:48,860
I didn't catch it.

630
01:07:53,060 --> 01:07:56,420
Thank you, my sweet baby.

631
01:08:01,700 --> 01:08:03,300
Will we get to work today, huh?

632
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:11,980
If you're this active, should I assign you
to your first project, Boss Lada?

633
01:08:13,360 --> 01:08:15,300
Right on my very first day?

634
01:08:17,359 --> 01:08:18,359
Aren't you ready.

635
01:08:19,899 --> 01:08:20,899
Yes, I am.

636
01:08:21,560 --> 01:08:22,560
Good girl.

637
01:08:24,160 --> 01:08:25,359
I'm just afraid I might fail.

638
01:08:26,000 --> 01:08:27,000
How about this?

639
01:08:29,760 --> 01:08:32,080
Why don't you try sitting
there first? See if you like it.

640
01:08:33,000 --> 01:08:34,000
Okay.

641
01:09:13,560 --> 01:09:14,939
Nam!

642
01:09:39,300 --> 01:09:40,340
So sweet.

643
01:09:59,200 --> 01:10:00,900
There she is.

644
01:10:01,700 --> 01:10:02,700
Did you find it?

645
01:10:07,560 --> 01:10:08,560
Thank you.

646
01:10:08,700 --> 01:10:09,960
You're amazing. Thank you.

647
01:10:32,300 --> 01:10:33,580
Do you want more?

648
01:10:44,930 --> 01:10:46,260
Good morning!

649
01:10:46,860 --> 01:10:48,600
Lada, you're early today.

650
01:10:50,130 --> 01:10:52,860
I have a meeting after this.

651
01:10:53,600 --> 01:10:57,040
I'll go back to Prachuap after the meeting.
So, I'm dropping by to check on Dad first.

652
01:11:00,260 --> 01:11:01,400
How is he doing?

653
01:11:04,760 --> 01:11:06,036
He's having more appetite.

654
01:11:06,060 --> 01:11:08,540
The PT will come in the
afternoon to give him therapy.

655
01:11:26,900 --> 01:11:28,160
How are you doing, Dad?

656
01:11:43,460 --> 01:11:44,460
Are you okay, Mum?

657
01:11:46,200 --> 01:11:47,360
Okay about what?

658
01:11:48,360 --> 01:11:51,900
If it's about you asking
me to look after your father,

659
01:11:53,100 --> 01:11:54,100
Yes, I'm okay.

660
01:11:55,130 --> 01:11:56,760
You have to tell me if you're not okay.

661
01:11:57,760 --> 01:11:59,860
We can always go back
to our home stay in Nan.

662
01:12:00,160 --> 01:12:01,960
We still have Rainy to
take care of him here.

663
01:12:08,060 --> 01:12:09,530
Seeing him like this,

664
01:12:10,860 --> 01:12:12,330
how could I leave him be?

665
01:12:25,360 --> 01:12:26,560
Oh, it's here?

666
01:12:27,700 --> 01:12:30,620
Yes, I showed it to your dad this morning.

667
01:12:37,100 --> 01:12:38,400
What did he say?

668
01:12:43,800 --> 01:12:45,060
As usual, right?

669
01:12:48,730 --> 01:12:54,900
That's what he's like. But deep down,
he's so proud of you.

670
01:13:05,660 --> 01:13:08,400
I'd better go to work then.

671
01:13:08,860 --> 01:13:12,000
If you need anything or want to talk
to me, you can always give me a call.

672
01:13:12,700 --> 01:13:13,700
Okay.

673
01:13:13,900 --> 01:13:14,900
Come, I'll walk you off.

674
01:13:17,760 --> 01:13:19,060
Say goodbye to your dad first.

675
01:13:26,560 --> 01:13:29,160
Dad, I'm off to work.

676
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:37,300
Please get well soon.

677
01:13:41,340 --> 01:13:42,540
Goodbye.

678
01:14:49,500 --> 01:14:50,500
Miss Preem.

679
01:14:52,200 --> 01:14:54,700
Oh, you finished so late.

680
01:14:56,860 --> 01:14:59,100
I need a bouquet of tulips.

681
01:14:59,300 --> 01:15:01,400
Is there still any shop open by this time?

682
01:15:02,300 --> 01:15:04,260
I'm afraid they're all closed.

683
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:06,060
Can it be tomorrow?

684
01:15:06,130 --> 01:15:07,756
I'll order one for you
first thing in the morning.

685
01:15:07,780 --> 01:15:09,730
Is it for Boss Lada?

686
01:15:10,300 --> 01:15:11,760
Tomorrow'll be too late.

687
01:15:12,360 --> 01:15:14,460
It's our 3-month wedding anniversary today.

688
01:15:14,620 --> 01:15:17,820
Whoa! It's been three months already?

689
01:15:19,460 --> 01:15:25,476
But if you go home empty-handed like this

690
01:15:25,500 --> 01:15:27,860
wouldn't Boss Lada get so mad at you?

691
01:15:30,500 --> 01:15:31,500
Really?

692
01:15:58,700 --> 01:16:01,020
She's quite reasonable.

693
01:16:01,780 --> 01:16:03,460
I'm sure she'd understand.

694
01:16:12,500 --> 01:16:13,500
I'm home, Babe.

695
01:16:21,160 --> 01:16:22,160
Have you eaten?

696
01:16:24,000 --> 01:16:25,000
Not yet.

697
01:16:25,200 --> 01:16:27,260
I came straight home after I finished work.

698
01:16:28,100 --> 01:16:30,600
Do you want me to fix
something for you to eat?

699
01:16:31,000 --> 01:16:32,960
You can go shower while waiting.

700
01:16:36,800 --> 01:16:38,000
Are you still working?

701
01:16:38,600 --> 01:16:41,356
Yes, but it's almost done now.

702
01:16:41,380 --> 01:16:44,980
I want to get it done as soon as I can
so that I can focus on something else.

703
01:16:49,700 --> 01:16:53,300
I'm sorry for coming home late.

704
01:16:53,860 --> 01:16:58,580
Didn't you tell me you have
a meeting with the supplier?

705
01:17:04,330 --> 01:17:05,330
It's good.

706
01:17:06,560 --> 01:17:08,460
My baby is talented as always.

707
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:19,600
There's one thing I
need to apologise to you.

708
01:17:20,930 --> 01:17:21,930
What is it?

709
01:17:24,340 --> 01:17:31,900
Well, I…forgot to buy flowers
for our 3-month wedding anniversary today.

710
01:17:35,960 --> 01:17:37,700
3-month wedding anniversary?

711
01:17:45,330 --> 01:17:47,580
Baby, I'm sorry!

712
01:17:50,530 --> 01:17:51,530
You forgot?

713
01:17:55,460 --> 01:17:58,420
So busy with work that
I've lost track of time.

714
01:18:02,260 --> 01:18:08,380
So, it turns out Boss Lada is
actually more workaholic than me.

715
01:18:09,940 --> 01:18:12,460
But I'm still not as good as you, Boss.

716
01:18:19,260 --> 01:18:25,100
Does that mean we won't get to celebrate,
our anniversary like last month?

717
01:18:26,900 --> 01:18:29,800
Last month, you took me out
to dinner at a fancy restaurant.

718
01:18:30,530 --> 01:18:33,330
It's my turn this time.

719
01:18:35,600 --> 01:18:39,100
Should I order from our hotel then?

720
01:18:46,760 --> 01:18:47,760
Here you go.

721
01:18:51,860 --> 01:18:53,180
Good vibes, right?

722
01:18:56,400 --> 01:18:59,060
This is the food you first cooked for me.

723
01:19:00,500 --> 01:19:02,760
You kept complaining it's useless though.

724
01:19:04,400 --> 01:19:05,660
But you still eat it anyway.

725
01:19:06,860 --> 01:19:08,940
That's because you made it for me.

726
01:19:10,660 --> 01:19:12,580
Aren't you afraid you'd
consume too much sodium?

727
01:19:14,260 --> 01:19:15,260
Hmm…

728
01:19:20,160 --> 01:19:23,330
Actually, I like to eat you more.

729
01:19:24,530 --> 01:19:26,730
But eating me won't make your stomach full.

730
01:19:28,400 --> 01:19:30,300
But it makes my heart full.

731
01:19:32,260 --> 01:19:34,160
I'm so lucky to have you.

732
01:19:38,560 --> 01:19:42,020
Do you think I'm mad?

733
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:50,260
Are you mad at me that I forgot
about our wedding anniversary?

734
01:19:52,900 --> 01:19:53,900
Yes.

735
01:19:56,730 --> 01:19:57,730
Just kidding.

736
01:19:57,940 --> 01:19:58,940
Geez!

737
01:19:59,330 --> 01:20:01,900
I'm not mad. I'm just worried…

738
01:20:02,860 --> 01:20:07,876
If I've given you too much
work or responsibilities.

739
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,740
So much that it makes
you lose track of time.

740
01:20:10,460 --> 01:20:12,300
I won't be so busy
after this project is done,

741
01:20:12,730 --> 01:20:15,130
which means I'll have more time for you.

742
01:20:16,560 --> 01:20:17,660
Me too.

743
01:20:19,100 --> 01:20:21,360
I'll try to spend time with
you as much as I can.

744
01:20:24,660 --> 01:20:32,660
Actually, we don't need to buy gifts
or do anything special for each other.

745
01:20:33,460 --> 01:20:36,780
Having you by my side is already enough.

746
01:20:38,260 --> 01:20:39,460
But I want it.

747
01:20:42,530 --> 01:20:43,530
Just kidding.

748
01:20:44,960 --> 01:20:49,360
Having you by my side is like
getting a special gift every day.

749
01:20:50,300 --> 01:20:52,300
Are we having a sweet-talking
competition or what?

750
01:20:54,560 --> 01:20:55,560
Sweet talking?

751
01:20:57,160 --> 01:20:59,800
If you mean whether
my lips are sweet or not,

752
01:21:00,960 --> 01:21:02,600
you'll have to ask yourself that.

753
01:21:03,200 --> 01:21:05,200
'Cause I've never tasted my own lips.

754
01:21:09,800 --> 01:21:11,000
I haven't bitten you yet.

755
01:21:12,700 --> 01:21:13,700
Ouch!

756
01:21:15,400 --> 01:21:17,930
Happy 3-month wedding anniversary, my baby.

757
01:21:21,660 --> 01:21:22,660
Now, eat.

758
01:21:23,560 --> 01:21:24,560
Thank you.

759
01:21:26,330 --> 01:21:27,740
Don't you want it too?

760
01:21:29,740 --> 01:21:30,900
Come on.

761
01:21:31,780 --> 01:21:34,660
Just one bite.

762
01:21:39,530 --> 01:21:40,530
Is it good.

763
01:21:41,130 --> 01:21:41,930
No.

764
01:21:42,100 --> 01:21:43,760
But you cooked it.

765
01:21:46,000 --> 01:21:47,876
Do you want to eat me tonight?

766
01:21:47,900 --> 01:21:48,900
Are you craving for me?

767
01:21:49,000 --> 01:21:50,860
It won't be just a bite this time.

768
01:21:54,600 --> 01:21:58,596
Our first package is a long stay
one-a dive and stay package.

769
01:21:58,620 --> 01:22:04,956
It's a 3-day-2-night stay on a luxury yacht
eligible for the VIP and private guests only.

770
01:22:04,980 --> 01:22:07,260
You can make a request
for your meals beforehand.

771
01:22:07,360 --> 01:22:09,800
Can you send the meal
list to Miss Fon then?

772
01:22:10,130 --> 01:22:12,260
Of course, Miss Preem
will take care of that for you.

773
01:22:12,530 --> 01:22:15,536
We'll also have a Full Moon party, completely
different from what you might've seen.

774
01:22:15,560 --> 01:22:19,700
It will be private. No outside guests
or clients are allowed to attend.

775
01:22:22,660 --> 01:22:25,800
As for the third package, I'll have
Miss Preem introduce it to you.

776
01:22:26,700 --> 01:22:27,700
Thank you, Miss Preem.

777
01:22:34,160 --> 01:22:36,300
Nam.

778
01:22:40,860 --> 01:22:41,860
It's lunchtime.

779
01:22:46,100 --> 01:22:47,530
Sorry, I forgot to tell you.

780
01:22:48,460 --> 01:22:51,200
I'm afraid you'll have
to eat lunch alone today.

781
01:22:52,160 --> 01:22:53,160
Why?

782
01:22:54,060 --> 01:22:55,930
I have to take care of the guests.

783
01:22:56,300 --> 01:22:59,000
Three big groups of them will
be coming for a check-in today.

784
01:23:01,900 --> 01:23:05,060
So, I guess I'll have to eat alone again.

785
01:23:09,960 --> 01:23:13,960
I'll try to wrap up work as fast as I can so
that I can spend a lot of time with you, okay?

786
01:23:16,800 --> 01:23:20,500
Do you know you're a workaholic now?

787
01:23:21,200 --> 01:23:22,556
Not as much as you.

788
01:23:22,580 --> 01:23:24,220
Nope, not true.

789
01:23:24,760 --> 01:23:25,960
You're worse than me.

790
01:23:30,000 --> 01:23:31,100
Nam.

791
01:24:09,560 --> 01:24:10,940
Nam.

792
01:24:37,530 --> 01:24:38,530
What are you doing?

793
01:24:39,660 --> 01:24:42,530
Blocking the sun for you.

794
01:24:55,300 --> 01:24:56,420
Are you sulking?

795
01:25:00,130 --> 01:25:02,130
I'm not someone who'd sulk.

796
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:09,160
You aren't?

797
01:25:09,900 --> 01:25:11,960
But your cheeks say otherwise.

798
01:25:12,730 --> 01:25:13,740
Let me see.

799
01:25:17,800 --> 01:25:19,300
So soft.

800
01:25:26,800 --> 01:25:27,800
Are we good now?

801
01:25:30,660 --> 01:25:31,700
Not yet.

802
01:25:45,760 --> 01:25:47,020
Are we good now?

803
01:25:48,660 --> 01:25:52,820
Don't leave me to eat alone so often, okay?

804
01:25:55,600 --> 01:25:58,100
I'll never leave you to eat alone again.

805
01:25:58,700 --> 01:26:00,740
And you'll always be my
first priority from now on.

806
01:26:19,700 --> 01:26:20,930
So sulky.

807
01:26:22,300 --> 01:26:23,580
I'm okay now.

808
01:26:27,100 --> 01:26:28,100
I'm not mad anymore!

809
01:26:28,860 --> 01:26:31,980
Really? Are you sure?

810
01:26:32,180 --> 01:26:34,300
Lada! You'll make us fall.

811
01:26:47,130 --> 01:26:52,260
This is Mr. Prasobchoke, the owner of an organiser
company \who'll be working with our hotel.

812
01:26:53,900 --> 01:26:54,577
Hello.

813
01:26:54,601 --> 01:26:55,800
This is Lada,

814
01:26:56,460 --> 01:26:58,600
one of the CEOs at the Watin Group.

815
01:26:59,200 --> 01:27:00,900
I'm glad we finally met.

816
01:27:01,660 --> 01:27:06,800
I'm terribly sorry I couldn't make it to
your wedding, Miss Apo and Miss Chonlada.

817
01:27:07,760 --> 01:27:10,530
May I take this opportunity
to congratulate you instead?

818
01:27:11,200 --> 01:27:12,660
Thank you.

819
01:27:13,130 --> 01:27:15,200
You must be very busy, Mr. Prasobchoke.

820
01:27:15,660 --> 01:27:17,380
Not often that I'd get a chance to see you.

821
01:27:18,800 --> 01:27:22,530
You'll get to see him
more often from now on.

822
01:27:23,060 --> 01:27:26,760
He'll be helping us at the new branch
which will have a grand opening soon.

823
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:29,000
We're counting on you.

824
01:27:29,500 --> 01:27:30,500
My pleasure indeed.

825
01:27:32,960 --> 01:27:34,436
Excuse me, Miss.

826
01:27:34,460 --> 01:27:38,220
One of the guests would like to talk to
you, Miss Chonlada. This way, please.

827
01:27:39,020 --> 01:27:41,260
Please excuse me then.

828
01:27:42,200 --> 01:27:43,200
Of course.

829
01:27:43,300 --> 01:27:44,560
I'll be back.

830
01:27:45,100 --> 01:27:46,100
I'll follow you soon.

831
01:27:46,530 --> 01:27:47,636
It's all right.

832
01:27:47,660 --> 01:27:50,180
You can stay here to
talk to Mr. Prasobchoke.

833
01:27:55,340 --> 01:27:56,340
Wait.

834
01:27:59,660 --> 01:28:01,500
Does the guest want to talk to Lada alone?

835
01:28:02,000 --> 01:28:03,000
Yes, Miss.

836
01:28:04,260 --> 01:28:05,260
It's a guy?

837
01:28:06,100 --> 01:28:07,100
Yes.

838
01:28:17,160 --> 01:28:20,100
Miss Apo, I heard you've been
married for quite some time, haven't you?

839
01:28:23,200 --> 01:28:24,200
Yes?

840
01:28:25,660 --> 01:28:27,600
Don't worry, Miss Chonlada won't disappear.

841
01:28:44,960 --> 01:28:48,580
Mr. Marwin? Hello.

842
01:28:48,700 --> 01:28:51,820
Hello, Miss Lada. Long time no see indeed.

843
01:28:52,420 --> 01:28:59,060
I think it's probably since my art exhibition at Miss
Apo's hotel-you were the one in charge back then.

844
01:29:00,020 --> 01:29:02,740
I never thought I'd get to see you here.

845
01:29:03,660 --> 01:29:04,900
How are you doing?

846
01:29:05,260 --> 01:29:06,260
I'm good, thank you.

847
01:29:06,730 --> 01:29:09,100
So, what matter brought
you to Hua Hin, Mr. Marwin?

848
01:29:09,260 --> 01:29:10,436
I'm here for a vacation.

849
01:29:10,460 --> 01:29:13,756
I've been looking for some inspiration.

850
01:29:13,780 --> 01:29:16,956
The exhibition owner happened to hear
about it and sent me an invitation card.

851
01:29:16,980 --> 01:29:19,900
And I'm the kind of person who
doesn't like to turn down people's offers.

852
01:29:20,530 --> 01:29:21,530
I see.

853
01:29:23,100 --> 01:29:27,100
But I'm glad I've decided to come today.

854
01:29:27,780 --> 01:29:30,540
At least, I get to meet someone I kn.

855
01:29:31,330 --> 01:29:32,356
Well, I'm here…

856
01:29:32,380 --> 01:29:34,876
Oh, excuse me.

857
01:29:34,900 --> 01:29:35,900
Yes, sir.

858
01:29:37,300 --> 01:29:40,916
Miss Lada, let's have a toast, shall we?

859
01:29:40,940 --> 01:29:43,380
For the occasion that we meet again.

860
01:29:44,730 --> 01:29:45,730
Thank you.

861
01:29:47,100 --> 01:29:49,620
Excuse me? Do you have fruit juice?

862
01:29:49,730 --> 01:29:51,716
I'm sorry. We only offer wine
and champagne in this corner.

863
01:29:51,740 --> 01:29:54,300
I can bring one for you if you
want. Please wait a moment, Miss.

864
01:29:54,460 --> 01:29:57,100
Never mind then. Thank you.

865
01:29:57,260 --> 01:29:58,260
Yes, Miss.

866
01:30:01,900 --> 01:30:03,060
Lada!

867
01:30:05,900 --> 01:30:09,420
There you are. I've been
looking for you everywhere.

868
01:30:10,800 --> 01:30:12,160
Hello, Miss Apo.

869
01:30:12,900 --> 01:30:16,580
I'm sorry I got too carried
away chatting with her.

870
01:30:18,060 --> 01:30:19,060
It's all right.

871
01:30:19,600 --> 01:30:22,780
Hello to you too, Mr…Marwin.

872
01:30:22,900 --> 01:30:25,380
What are you guys
talking about? It seems fun.

873
01:30:26,000 --> 01:30:28,400
Are you almost done now?

874
01:30:28,900 --> 01:30:32,180
I can go wait outside so
you two can finish talking.

875
01:30:33,540 --> 01:30:34,730
It's okay, Miss Apo.

876
01:30:34,900 --> 01:30:36,360
Please come join us too.

877
01:30:36,500 --> 01:30:37,820
It'll be fun to have more people.

878
01:30:41,130 --> 01:30:42,130
Okay.

879
01:30:42,960 --> 01:30:48,596
Miss Lada, I'll have an exhibition of
my paintings in Bangkok next month.

880
01:30:48,620 --> 01:30:51,076
Please kindly accept
my invitation in advance.

881
01:30:51,100 --> 01:30:53,780
I'll send you the VIP
invitation card afterwards.

882
01:30:53,960 --> 01:30:56,200
Will it portray only your work, Mr. Marwin?

883
01:30:56,700 --> 01:30:59,916
Yes. I remember you once
told me you like my paintings.

884
01:30:59,940 --> 01:31:02,076
And you're also into art.

885
01:31:02,100 --> 01:31:03,660
I don't want you to miss it.

886
01:31:04,730 --> 01:31:07,600
It's true that I appreciate art,
but someone here loves it more.

887
01:31:08,960 --> 01:31:10,060
Isn't that right, Nam?

888
01:31:12,460 --> 01:31:17,220
Yes, I also like art
but less than I like you.

889
01:31:19,130 --> 01:31:21,660
Then, I guess I'll have to
ask for two invitation cards.

890
01:31:23,400 --> 01:31:27,000
Of course. I'll have two invitation
cards delivered to you, Miss Lada.

891
01:31:28,160 --> 01:31:30,930
Excellent. We can find a nice
place for our date in Bangkok too.

892
01:31:31,260 --> 01:31:34,196
Good idea. It's been a while
since we last went there.

893
01:31:34,220 --> 01:31:36,100
We've been too busy working in Hua Hin.

894
01:31:36,460 --> 01:31:40,960
Right? There're so many places
I want to go on a date with you there.

895
01:31:42,200 --> 01:31:45,060
Well then, I'm afraid I'll
have to excuse myself.

896
01:31:45,300 --> 01:31:47,900
I'll have my secretary take
care of your invitation cards.

897
01:31:48,200 --> 01:31:49,330
Yes, thank you.

898
01:31:51,560 --> 01:31:52,560
Thank you.

899
01:31:56,330 --> 01:31:57,400
Jealous, aren't you?

900
01:31:59,860 --> 01:32:00,940
No, I'm not.

901
01:32:01,660 --> 01:32:02,740
Liar.

902
01:32:03,700 --> 01:32:05,000
What were you two talking about?

903
01:32:06,140 --> 01:32:07,460
Just this and that.

904
01:32:09,730 --> 01:32:10,730
Not jealous, huh?

905
01:32:11,540 --> 01:32:12,940
Okay, not jealous.

906
01:32:13,560 --> 01:32:14,700
Just you wait.

907
01:32:15,130 --> 01:32:16,690
I thought you said you weren't jealous.

908
01:32:18,000 --> 01:32:20,940
Were you? Were you jealous?

909
01:32:30,200 --> 01:32:31,360
Look, Babe.

910
01:32:34,200 --> 01:32:38,730
Mr. Marwin just sent us his
painting called 'Sea &amp; Tide'.

911
01:32:39,400 --> 01:32:41,360
Don't you think it's beautiful?

912
01:32:47,400 --> 01:32:51,420
Hey, aren't you going to talk to me?

913
01:32:51,760 --> 01:32:54,760
You were so smitten with me
at the party right in front of Mr. Marwin.

914
01:32:57,100 --> 01:33:02,380
If you really love his painting,
just admire it all you want.

915
01:33:05,420 --> 01:33:06,420
Hold on!

916
01:33:11,330 --> 01:33:13,130
I won't do that anymore.

917
01:33:13,930 --> 01:33:18,130
Next time, if he tries to talk to me, I'll
walk away and forget all my manners.

918
01:33:20,100 --> 01:33:22,300
So that you won't be sulking
and mad at me like this.

919
01:33:24,220 --> 01:33:25,260
I don't like-.

920
01:33:29,000 --> 01:33:32,400
I just don't like it when I
can't manage my own feelings.

921
01:33:33,660 --> 01:33:34,660
What do you mean?

922
01:33:35,960 --> 01:33:38,600
This feeling-does it
mean I'm being jealous?

923
01:33:47,260 --> 01:33:48,700
So jealous.

924
01:33:53,330 --> 01:33:57,160
I don't want you to think that I'm
being emotional and unreasonable.

925
01:33:58,060 --> 01:34:00,060
Why? It's kind of cute.

926
01:34:03,220 --> 01:34:07,220
You getting jealous is so adorable!

927
01:34:11,340 --> 01:34:12,340
That's it.

928
01:34:46,760 --> 01:34:47,760
So beautiful.

929
01:34:50,000 --> 01:34:51,330
Only the painting?

930
01:34:53,100 --> 01:34:54,400
My wife too.

931
01:34:59,100 --> 01:35:00,300
Can you get up first?

932
01:35:05,730 --> 01:35:07,740
Let me sit too.

933
01:35:17,660 --> 01:35:18,660
Do you like it?

934
01:35:19,360 --> 01:35:20,960
Why this picture.

935
01:35:25,100 --> 01:35:26,500
I like the sea.

936
01:35:27,530 --> 01:35:32,560
It holds so many memories,
and it's also where our love has begun.

937
01:35:41,300 --> 01:35:45,460
A pink tulip and a sunflower.

938
01:35:47,060 --> 01:35:52,660
Don't they remind you
of a daughter and a son?

939
01:35:56,660 --> 01:35:58,260
That's brilliant.

940
01:36:00,860 --> 01:36:05,220
If we were to have kids, what
do you want to name them?

941
01:36:08,960 --> 01:36:12,220
I want to name them
'Talay' (♪means the sea).

942
01:36:12,760 --> 01:36:13,760
Talay?

943
01:36:15,960 --> 01:36:17,700
What about their first name?

944
01:36:19,060 --> 01:36:21,600
It's so sudden I can't
think of anything right now.

945
01:36:22,400 --> 01:36:26,100
Don't tell me you already
have some names in mind.

946
01:36:28,540 --> 01:36:36,100
If it's a boy, I'd like to
name him 'Chonlatarn'.

947
01:36:36,960 --> 01:36:38,300
What if it's a girl?

948
01:36:39,530 --> 01:36:46,060
Then, I'd name her
'Ananda'... it means joyfulness.

949
01:36:46,900 --> 01:36:47,900
Do you like that?

950
01:36:48,560 --> 01:36:49,360
Yes.

951
01:36:49,500 --> 01:36:54,260
I'm combining your name with mine.

952
01:36:57,700 --> 01:36:59,660
But there's also this
name that I like the most.

953
01:37:00,160 --> 01:37:02,860
There's more? What is it?

954
01:37:04,700 --> 01:37:05,860
It's Chonlada

955
01:37:07,800 --> 01:37:10,540
a stream of water that
fills my heart with love.

956
01:37:11,960 --> 01:37:15,540
Thank you for making me
know what true love is like.

957
01:37:18,860 --> 01:37:23,340
Me too. Thank you for coming
into my life and making it meaningful.

958
01:37:27,460 --> 01:37:31,580
♫ You're the one that change my life ♫

959
01:37:32,180 --> 01:37:36,356
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone ♫

960
01:37:36,380 --> 01:37:38,756
♫ Thank you so much ♫

961
01:37:38,780 --> 01:37:41,916
♫ For making my life meaningful ♫

962
01:37:41,940 --> 01:37:47,740
♫ How lucky I am to have you ♫

963
01:37:52,420 --> 01:37:58,380
[The End]

964
01:38:19,140 --> 01:38:24,636
♫ Since the day you came
into my life, I start to realise… ♫

965
01:38:24,660 --> 01:38:28,796
♫ What it's like to be
someone who matters ♫

966
01:38:28,820 --> 01:38:34,756
♫ Feeling so warm whenever I see you ♫

967
01:38:34,780 --> 01:38:37,516
♫ Who often stays close to me ♫

968
01:38:37,540 --> 01:38:42,396
♫ I just want you to know ♫

969
01:38:42,420 --> 01:38:49,236
♫ This feeling that's happening inside ♫

970
01:38:49,260 --> 01:38:52,316
♫ I don't want to hide it anymore ♫

971
01:38:52,340 --> 01:38:56,060
♫ I guess I'll have to tell you ♫

972
01:38:56,740 --> 01:39:00,780
♫ You're the one that change my life ♫

973
01:39:01,500 --> 01:39:05,756
♫ Make me feel more important than anyone ♫

974
01:39:05,780 --> 01:39:11,076
♫ Thank you so much for
making my life meaningful ♫

975
01:39:11,100 --> 01:39:17,420
♫ How lucky I am to have you ♫

976
01:39:21,620 --> 01:39:27,420
[Waves of Deception]
